🔐 Security Insight

Bash scripts are powerful and can:

Modify system files
Start/stop services
Delete or create resources
Automate deployments
DevOps best practices:
Always review scripts before execution
Avoid running unknown scripts as root
Use least privilege principle
Store scripts in version control (Git)
Validate input in production scripts
